   <note>A letter by Zebadiah Pike, Captain, to James Robertson in Nashville, Tennessee. Pike seeks direction in dealings with Chickasaw Indians. Pike relates that Captain Parks killed Cherokee men and took prisoners in May. Pike attempted to speak to Chickasaws about a certain prisoner, but it is not clear how the talks were resolved. He asks for a "line" about what to do from Robertson.</note>
